## The First 90 Days

The first three months of any SEO engagement are the most important. They set the technical foundation, establish the content architecture, and build the strategic understanding of your specific market.

**Month 1 — Audit, strategy, and foundations.**

The engagement opens with a comprehensive technical and content audit. I review your site's crawl health, indexation status, Core Web Vitals, existing content quality, current ranking profile, and competitor landscape in detail. This is not a tool-generated checklist — it is a manual assessment of your specific situation.

By the end of month one you will have: a prioritised technical fix list, a 12-month topical map, your first set of content briefs, and a clear assessment of your most immediate ranking opportunities. If there are quick wins — technical fixes that can improve rankings within weeks — those are actioned first.

**Month 2 — Technical resolution and content launch.**

Technical priorities from the audit are implemented. The first tranche of content briefs is delivered to your team (or produced directly, depending on your setup). We begin building the internal linking structure that concentrates authority toward your highest-value commercial pages.

Initial ranking movements are typically visible by the end of month two for lower-competition queries and longer-tail terms. These are leading indicators — not the main event.

**Month 3 — Iteration and early signals.**

By month three the technical foundation is stable, the first content cluster is live, and Google has had time to evaluate the changes. We review what is moving, analyse what is not, and refine the strategy accordingly.

Most clients see meaningful ranking improvements for mid-competition queries in this window. For highly competitive terms — particularly in professional services, legal, financial, and technology sectors — the 6–12 month window is realistic for page-one positions.

