## What You Need to Bring

The honest truth: I can develop the strategy, but organic growth requires execution capacity on your side.

**Content production.** The content briefs I produce are detailed and structured for efficient writing — but your team (or a writer we agree on) needs to produce the content. If you have no content production capacity, a retainer will underperform. We can discuss managed content production as an add-on.

**Development access.** Technical SEO fixes require someone who can make changes to your website. This might be your in-house developer, a freelancer, or your agency's dev team. You need this resource available on a reasonable turnaround — not a four-week ticket queue.

**Decision-making authority.** The monthly strategy sessions are collaborative. Someone in your business needs to be able to make decisions — approve content topics, sign off on site changes, set priorities — without a three-week approval chain.

**A 6–12 month horizon.** [SEO compounds over time](/blog/how-long-does-seo-take). The businesses that see the best results commit to the methodology for long enough to let it work. If you need search results within 8 weeks, paid search is the right tool — not SEO.

