## Why an Independent Consultant Rather Than an Agency

At an agency, a £2,500 monthly retainer covers: account management salary, office overhead, business development costs, junior staff time, and — if you are fortunate — occasional senior attention. The person who pitched you is working across 20 other accounts.

With an independent consultant, £2,500 buys senior-level strategy and direct implementation oversight — one person, focused, with a deliberately small client list.

The trade-off is scale: if you need thirty blog posts produced per month, you need a team. If you need rigorous strategy applied with genuine attention to your specific situation, an independent consultant delivers better value at this budget level.

[More on how consultants compare to agencies →](/blog/seo-consultant-vs-seo-agency)

